spanGrp.span: ‘A small thing called him to go for a ride.
(_) Jirö yulei të í kiá ñãyulö
As they were going their way,
but the frog did not see them.
ñerö buke buke të mẽnẽbi jie ka wã sunẽ
So they crashed against a big stone;
ñerö jak kajki keyege mẽ í kenã'
the frog began to cry because he [thought that] he had killed them.
Ñerö buke të buke jiñã'-wã-nã jie nẽ të í ktá-wa rö
The mouse told him it was his fault;
(_) Koño të í shá-nã jie í rö
but they managed to grab it so he could not die;
ñerö jie-wa të í gugá-nẽ (_) ka í dö-wö-wã' kueinga
then uh he called an ambulance, which took him along;
ñerö (_) ele ambulansia kiá-ite wã í mẽnẽtse-mĩ
then uh he called an ambulance, which took him along;
je rö wayinã'-nã karro dé wã mẽnẽtse-mĩ
There the frog said to him that/oh, no I mean the mouse rose and grabbed a branch.
Jeska buke í shá ĩã-ñã ele ah no/ koño bötsa-nã'-ka kaljula (_) komĩ' mẽnẽbi jẽk gugá cha
Then the car was in bad condition;
ñerö ka/ karro jirö (_) pe sigö-glo je (extra) je je blali klabe-ka (_) sulölë-wã
so he told him [the ambulance driver] that the one who had hit it [the small thing] had taken it away already.
Ñerö je ĩã í shá-ite-nã je nẽ të í í shká-wã kueinga í mẽnẽtse-mĩ í wã
The mouse told him that he had killed him.
ñerö koño koño të shá ĩã-nã (_) ñẽ jebi (_) jie ñẽ rö í ke (m) í ktá-wã rö
Then the small thing appeared all wrapped up;
Ñerö ele ele yulei dajũ pamo-lë köũ
so he saw him, took care of him;
ñerö jie të í sũã' jie të í kunãnã'
jie të í sũã ñerö (_) böi-nã'-nẽ
So he told him that whenever he was on the road he should look carefully because there might be something.
kueinga e-gla shá-nẽ ĩã kuando jie të nala krusawẽ-gẽ-sã'-ra-nã jirö sũẽ-ite-nã jirö dajũ kueinga
The small mouse was coming, and the mouse took him along;
koño yulei (_) dajũ-nẽ je wã í mẽnẽtse-mĩ jela
the three of them went away.’
